</ul>','<p>The <strong>laser receiver</strong> is a sensor that detects the rotating laser beam from the <strong>transmitter</strong> (also called a rotary laser level) set up on a tripod. As the laser sweeps across the field, the receiver captures the beam and determines if the implement blade is above, below, or on the reference elevation. It then sends this height information to the <strong>control box</strong>, which adjusts the implement hydraulics to maintain precise grading.</p>','[\"7651769146898_website img 7.jpg\",\"3331769152042_HD Rec.jpg\"]',NULL,'1','2026-01-23 05:41:38','2026-01-23 07:07:22',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
